{
  "texts": [
    "Parameter reduction in soft setsParameter reduction is a well-established branch within rough set theory.",
    "As in that case, in the framework of soft set theory it has a practical importance: its goal is the elimination of redundant parameters without affecting the optimal decisions.",
    "Since [171] defined the idea of reducing soft sets, a number of scholars have investigated this problem.",
    "Chen et al. [81] argued that another concept was better suited for this purpose.",
    "Kong et al. [149] contributed to the problem with an algorithm of normal parameter reduction."
  ]
}